text: The #Mississippi Senate has confirmed one if its own, retiring Sen. Videt Carmichael, to serve on the board of Meridian Community College. He is not here today, so did not vote on his own nomination. #msleg

text: #Mississippi Gov. Phil Bryant signs bill to ban most abortions after a fetal heartbeat is detected. It is set to become law July 1. The Center for Reproductive Rights says it will sue to try to block the law. #msleg #abortion

text: Rep. Ronnie Crudup Jr. of Jackson was sworn in to the #Mississippi House today. He won a special election last week to succeed former Rep. Adrienne Wooten, who is now a circuit judge. The current House term ends in January. #msleg
author: EWagsterPettus

text: Rep. Solomon Osborne of Greenwood was sworn in as a member of the #Mississippi House today, after winning a special election last week to succeed former Rep. Willie Perkins, who is now a chancery judge. The current House term ends in January. #msleg
